ReconName21_0CAF=21_0C
ReconPT21_0CAF=SUBJECT: Agency File on the ND133\nUPLOADED: 30/03/06; 04:23:45\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\n
ReconFT21_0CAF=SUBJECT: Agency File on the ND133\nUPLOADED: 30/03/06; 04:23:45\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\n\n\nNOTES:\nI'm cramming this together quickly from the Saulnier website and my high school French, so forgive me if any of their pseudo-Christian weirdness sneaks through.  The ND133 appears to be the budget model.  Higher-paying customers can get their whole bodies frozen, but if funds are tight, (less than around 15K U.S.,) a customer can get his brain scooped from his skull, deposited in an ND 133 (Naivre D'Espirit + 133 degrees Kelvin) about the size of a breadbox, and vacuum sealed frozen.  Even if there's a prolonged power outage (they subtly suggest the apocalypse here,) the vacuum seal of the ND 133 will keep the "passenger" safely frozen for several hundred years.  They call it a "private coach for the soul."\n(Author: Grimsdottir)

ReconName21_0DAF=21_0D
ReconPT21_0DAF=SUBJECT: Agency File on Francois Coldeboeuf\nUPLOADED: 30/03/06; 04:29:03\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\nFULL NAME: Francois Coulon Coldeboeuf\n
ReconFT21_0DAF=SUBJECT: Agency File on Francois Coldeboeuf\nUPLOADED: 30/03/06; 04:29:03\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\nFULL NAME: Francois Coulon Coldeboeuf\nKNOWN ALIASES: None\nDOB: 18/02/80\nHEIGHT: 6'2"\nWEIGHT:.173 lbs.\nHAIR: Black\nEYES: Brown\nCITIZENSHIP: French\nAREA OF OPERATION: Paris\nASSOCIATIONS: Security Guard, Saulnier Cryogenics Lab\n\n\nRELEVANT HISTORY:\n\n29/02/03-\nArrested for Invasion of Privacy, charges later dropped.\n\n09/01/05 - CURRENT:\nEmployed by Saulnier Cryogenics.\n\nNOTES:\nLooks like M. Coldeboeuf is nothing more than a hapless bystander.  The arrest in '03 was basically for voyeurism, Francois took a picture when he should have politely averted his gaze.  He's got bad instincts and bad luck, but seems like an okay guy.\n(Author: Grimsdottir) 

ReconName22_0AAF=22_0A
ReconPT22_0AAF=SUBJECT: Agency File on Norman Soth\nUPLOADED: 02/04/06; 21:54:18\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\nFULL NAME: Norman Washington Soth\n
ReconFT22_0AAF=SUBJECT: Agency File on Norman Soth\nUPLOADED: 02/04/06; 21:54:18\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\nFULL NAME: Norman Washington Soth\nKNOWN ALIASES: mortified_penguin, Jonathan Poindexter, Richard Arbor, Rizal Ariyanto\nDOB: 07/08/61\nHEIGHT: 6'0"\nWEIGHT: 183 lbs.\nHAIR: Brown / Balding\nEYES: Brown\nCITIZENSHIP: Unknown (multiple forged documents)\nAREA OF OPERATION: Indonesia / East Timor / Highly Mobile\nASSOCIATIONS: Darah Dan Doa; possibly CIA; possibly Kopassus (Indonesian Special Forces)\n\n\nRELEVANT HISTORY:\n\n07/08/61 - 19/03/72-\nCitizen of the United States.\n\n1972 - 1981-\nResident of Cambodia, Myanmar, Hong Kong, then Indonesia (Military family.)\n\n18/02/82-\nFirst CIA contact, approached by Agency Operative Kopple as a potential asset for Operation RED BEARD.\n\n06/06/83-\nApplies for Indonesian citizenship.\n\n05/07/83-\nEnters CIA asset payroll.\n\n
ReconFT22_0AAF1=24/07/83-\nEnters Kopassus training program.  (History with the Kopassus is vague.  There is no record of him either completing or dropping out of the program.)\n\n18/12/84-\nNorman Soth's parents die in a hotel Fire in Jakarta.\n\n1985 - 1992-\nReturn to the United States, residencies in Virginia, California, and Arizona. (Still on a CIA payroll)\n\n10/10/93- Returns to Indonesia.\n25/12/94-\nEnters Jakarta hospital with "severe damage to right leg and face."  Soth lost his earlobes and three fingers.  He never revealed to authorities who was responsible.\n\n02/03/95-\nFirst contact with the Darah Dan Doa.\n\n12/08/95-\nFirst contact with Suhadi Sadono, (as Richard Arbor.)\n\n04/05/98-\nSoth loses CIA funding.  (Intercepted chatter suggests increased involvement in Sadono's heroin business.)\n\n04/09/00 - 19/09/00-\nTrip to Paris, purpose unknown.\n\n07/01/02 - 12/02/02-\nTrip to Germany and Turkey.\n\n
ReconFT22_0AAF2=12/05/05 - 25/05/05-\nTrip to Virginia, USA.  Funds diverted to accounts linked to a Private Military Corporation.\n\nNOTES:\nI wish we knew more about the CIA's Operation Red Beard, it would clear up a lot of Soth's history.  As it stands, we've got no idea whether or not he's one of the good guys.  My guess is, he's a "Freedom Fighter" who became a "Terrorist" when the U.S. pulled a 180 on the Indonesia / East Timor situation.\n(Author: Grimsdottir) 

ReconName31_0AAF=31_0A
ReconPT31_0AAF=SUBJECT: Agency File on Dahlia Tal\nUPLOADED: 05/04/06; 01:02:13\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\nFULL NAME: Dahlia Suleiman Tal\n
ReconFT31_0AAF=SUBJECT: Agency File on Dahlia Tal\nUPLOADED: 05/04/06; 01:02:13\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\nFULL NAME: Dahlia Suleiman Tal\nKNOWN ALIASES: Manal Daher\nDOB: 11/08/68\nHEIGHT: 5'10"\nWEIGHT: 139 lbs.\nHAIR: Black\nEYES: Brown\nCITIZENSHIP: Israeli\nAREA OF OPERATION: Israel / West Bank / Lebanon / Highly Mobile\nASSOCIATIONS: Shin Bet (Israeli Secret Police,) "Grasp of the Corpse" (Syrian Terrorist Cell)\n\n\nRELEVANT HISTORY:\n\n11/08/84 - 10/08/86-\nIsraeli Nahal (Pioneer Fighting Youth)\n\n11/08/86 - 08/03/96-\nIsraeli Defense Force\n\n09/03/96-\nBegins MOSAD training program.\n\n04/11/97-\nRecruited for Shin Bet\n\n28/02/98 - 12/04/00 -\nAgent exchange program with British Secret Service.\n\n14/04/00 -\nCURRENT: Too much Shin Bet static for dependable information.\n\nNOTES:\n"Grasp of the Corpse" sounds more heroic in Arabic, or so I've been told.  If we were arranging a pit fight between Dahlia and a rottweiler, I'd put my money on Dahlia and wouldn't bother naming the dog.\n(Author: Grimsdottir) 

ReconName31_0BAF=31_0B
ReconPT31_0BAF=SUBJECT: Agency File on Shin Bet / Mossad\nUPLOADED: 05/04/06; 01:02:13\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\n
ReconFT31_0BAF=SUBJECT: Agency File on Shin Bet / Mossad\nUPLOADED: 05/04/06; 01:02:13\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\n\n\nNOTES:\nI'm sure you're familiar with Shin Bet and Mossad.  Mossad is Israel's more publicly acknowledged intelligence agency.  Shin Bet is the secret police, handling the less savory tasks, like interrogations (torture,) psy ops (torture,) and public relations (torture.)  The recent political climate and U.S. approach to international affairs has only encouraged Shin Bet (we sometimes pass along suspects for interrogation that our rules won't allow us to break.)\n(Author: Grimsdottir) 

ReconName31_0CAF=31_0C
ReconPT31_0CAF=SUBJECT: Map of the Geula District\nUPLOADED: 05/04/06; 01:02:13\nSOURCE: Grimsdottir\n
